Local artists, crafters and members of the public are invited to a Streetopia event in Observatory on Saturday 25 November.  It will take place at the community centre, on the village green and along a stretch of Lower Main Road from 10:00 to 18:00.  The streets will be open to pedestrians and cyclists, buskers and performers.  The event is hosted in a partnership between AfrikaBurn, OBSID and the Observatory Civic Association. Residents of Observatory, Salt River, Woodstock and surrounds will get a chance to exhibit their art and craft, host market stalls and dress up for a day of pageant.  According to the organisers, artworks and mutant vehicles from AfrikaBurn will be on display. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  